Apache Guacamole is a clientless remote desktop gateway that allows you to access systems via RDP, VNC, and SSH directly through a web browser.
It requires no additional software on the client side, making remote access simple and platform-independent.

-------------------------------------------------

Stack:
Apache Guacamole (Docker)
guacd
MySQL / MariaDB

-------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT!

Run the following commands to initialise DB after deployment:

Powershell:
docker run --rm guacamole/guacamole /opt/guacamole/bin/initdb.sh --mysql > initdb.sql
Get-Content .\initdb.sql | docker exec -i guac-mariadb mariadb -u root -pguacrootpass guacamole_db